---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="About" description="About forHumanity.art - an artist collective building open tools for reflection, healing, and growth.">
  <section class="about-hero py-16">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="text-center">About forHumanity.art</h1>
      
      <div class="about-content">
        <div class="message-card">
          <h2>A Message from Human #1</h2>
          <p>
            Hello! This if forHumanity an art collective, 
            forHumanity.art began as a simple idea: what if we built technology that that worked with ai to 
            prioritize reflection, healing, and growth over engagement, addiction, and profit?
          </p>
          
          <p>
            We believe in the power of small experiments, gentle technology, and 
            human-centered design. We are building tools that we wish existed—tools that 
            help us become more intentional, reflective, and connected to our values.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            This collective is open to anyone who shares these values. Whether you're a developer, designer, writer, or 
            just someone who cares about these ideas, there's a place for you here.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="values-section">
          <h2>Our Values</h2>
          
          <div class="values-grid">
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Transparency</h3>
              <p>
                We believe in open-source development, clear communication, and 
                honest reflection. Our code, our process, and our thinking are all 
                open for anyone to see and contribute to.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Curiosity</h3>
              <p>
                We approach problems with a spirit of experimentation and wonder. 
                We're not afraid to try new things, learn from failure, and iterate 
                on our ideas.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="value-card">
              <h3>Care</h3>
              <p>
                We build technology with care—care for the people who use it, care 
                for the communities it affects, and care for the world it exists in. 
                We prioritize ethical sustainability over rapid growth.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="join-section text-center py-8">
          <h2>Join Us</h2>
          <p>
            forHumanity.art is an open collective. We welcome contributors of all kinds—
            developers, designers, writers, thinkers, and anyone who cares about building 
            more humane technology.
          </p>
          
          <a href="/contribute" class="btn mt-4">How to Contribute</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .about-content {
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .message-card {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }
  
  .values-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }
  
  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }
  
  .value-card {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  
  .join-section {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
